Date: Thu, 29 May 2025 11:07:24 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: stmmac: make sure that ptp_rate is not 0 before
 configuring EST
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: cbefe2ffa7784525ec5d008ba87c7add19ec631a
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: CVE-2025-38125 bsc#1245710

[ Before c3f3b97238f6fd ("net: stmmac: Refactor EST implementation") refactoring.
  No message printed because there's no net_device available.  ]

If the ptp_rate recorded earlier in the driver happens to be 0, this
bogus value will propagate up to EST configuration, where it will
trigger a division by 0.

Prevent this division by 0 by adding the corresponding check and error
code.

Suggested-by: Maxime Chevallier <maxime.chevallier@bootlin.com>
Signed-off-by: Alexis Lothor√© <alexis.lothore@bootlin.com>
Fixes: 8572aec3d0dc ("net: stmmac: Add basic EST support for XGMAC")
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250529-stmmac_tstamp_div-v4-2-d73340a794d5@bootlin.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac5.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac5.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac5.c
@@ -597,6 +597,9 @@ int dwmac5_est_configure(void __iomem *i
 	int i, ret = 0x0;
 	u32 ctrl;
 
+	if (!ptp_rate)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	ret |= dwmac5_est_write(ioaddr, BTR_LOW, cfg->btr[0], false);
 	ret |= dwmac5_est_write(ioaddr, BTR_HIGH, cfg->btr[1], false);
 	ret |= dwmac5_est_write(ioaddr, TER, cfg->ter, false);
